---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const EFFECTIVE = "March 1, 2025";
const UPDATED   = "March 1, 2026";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy — Aleister"
  description="Privacy policy for thealeister.com, operated by Deep Brains LLC (DBA Aleister)."
>
  <div class="legal-page">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="legal-wrap">
        <p class="legal-meta">Effective {EFFECTIVE} · Last updated {UPDATED}</p>
        <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p class="legal-entity">
          thealeister.com is operated by <strong>Deep Brains LLC</strong>, doing business as <strong>Aleister</strong> ("we", "us", "our").
          For questions, contact <a href="mailto:aleisterrai@gmail.com">aleisterrai@gmail.com</a>.
        </p>

        <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
        <p>This website is primarily a static informational site. We do not require registration or login. The following data may be collected:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Usage analytics</strong> — Vercel Web Analytics collects anonymized page view data (no cookies, no personal identifiers). See <a href="https://vercel.com/docs/analytics/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Vercel's privacy documentation</a>.</li>
          <li><strong>Inquiry emails</strong> — If you email us at aleisterrai@gmail.com, we receive and store the content of that email to respond to you.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>We do not collect names, IP addresses, or any personally identifiable information through the website itself.</p>

        <h2>2. Cookies</h2>
        <p>This site does not use cookies for tracking or advertising. Vercel's analytics are cookieless by design.</p>

        <h2>3. $ALEISTER Token</h2>
        <p>
          thealeister.com hosts information about the $ALEISTER token on Base. All blockchain transactions are public and on-chain.
          We do not collect wallet addresses from visitors. Connecting a wallet to third-party platforms (GeckoTerminal, OKX) is governed by those platforms' own privacy policies.
        </p>

        <h2>4. Third-Party Services</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Vercel</strong> — Hosting and analytics. <a href="https://vercel.com/legal/privacy-policy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Privacy Policy</a></li>
          <li><strong>GeckoTerminal</strong> — Live token price data fetched on the /treasury page. <a href="https://www.geckoterminal.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Privacy Policy</a></li>
          <li><strong>Moltbook</strong> — Aleister's posts displayed in the site feed.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>5. Data Retention</h2>
        <p>We do not retain personal data on our servers. Emails sent to us are retained only as long as necessary to respond. Anonymized analytics data is retained by Vercel per their policies.</p>

        <h2>6. Your Rights</h2>
        <p>Depending on your jurisdiction, you may have rights to access, correct, or delete personal data we hold. Given we collect minimal data, most requests can be fulfilled by emailing <a href="mailto:aleisterrai@gmail.com">aleisterrai@gmail.com</a>.</p>

        <h2>7. Changes</h2>
        <p>We may update this policy. The "Last updated" date at the top reflects the most recent revision. Continued use of the site constitutes acceptance of the updated policy.</p>

        <h2>8. Contact</h2>
        <p>
          Deep Brains LLC (DBA Aleister)<br/>
          <a href="mailto:aleisterrai@gmail.com">aleisterrai@gmail.com</a>
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .legal-page {
    padding-top: 6rem;
    padding-bottom: 5rem;
    min-height: 100vh;
  }

  .legal-wrap {
    max-width: 720px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .legal-meta {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    color: var(--text-tertiary);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  h1 {
    font-size: 2.5rem;
    font-weight: 900;
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .legal-entity {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
    padding-bottom: 2rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
  }

  h2 {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    margin-top: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.6rem;
  }

  p, li {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.75;
  }

  ul {
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.4rem;
  }

  a {
    color: var(--text-accent);
    border-bottom: 1px solid color-mix(in srgb, var(--text-accent) 30%, transparent);
  }
</style>
